#. <section class="sutta" id="an4.8"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "an4.8:0.1"
msgid "Aṅguttara Nikāya 4"
msgstr "Numbered Discourses 4"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "an4.8:0.2"
msgid "1. Bhaṇḍagāmavagga"
msgstr "1. At Bhaṇḍa Village"

#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "an4.8:0.3"
msgid "8. Vesārajjasutta"
msgstr "8. Self-assured"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli2.9"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "an4.8:1.1"
msgid ""
"“Cattārimāni, bhikkhave, tathāgatassa vesārajjāni, yehi vesārajjehi "
"samannāgato tathāgato āsabhaṃ ṭhānaṃ paṭijānāti, parisāsu sīhanādaṃ nadati, "
"brahmacakkaṃ pavatteti."
msgstr ""
"“Mendicants, a Realized One has four kinds of self-assurance. With these he "
"claims the bull’s place, roars his lion’s roar in the assemblies, and turns "
"the holy wheel."

msgctxt "an4.8:1.2"
msgid "Katamāni cattāri?"
msgstr "What four?"

msgctxt "an4.8:1.3"
msgid ""
"‘“Sammāsambuddhassa te paṭijānato ime dhammā anabhisambuddhā”ti tatra vata "
"maṃ samaṇo vā brāhmaṇo vā devo vā māro vā brahmā vā koci vā lokasmiṃ "
"sahadhammena paṭicodessatī’ti nimittametaṃ, bhikkhave, na samanupassāmi."
msgstr ""
"I see no reason for anyone—whether ascetic, brahmin, god, Māra, or Brahmā, "
"or anyone else in the world—to legitimately scold me, saying: ‘You claim to "
"be fully awakened, but you don’t understand these things.’"

#. VAR: Etamahaṃ → etampahaṃ (bj, s1-3, km, pts1)
msgctxt "an4.8:1.4"
msgid ""
"Etamahaṃ, bhikkhave, nimittaṃ asamanupassanto khemappatto abhayappatto "
"vesārajjappatto viharāmi."
msgstr "Since I see no such reason, I live secure, fearless, and assured."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "an4.8:2.1"
msgid ""
"‘“Khīṇāsavassa te paṭijānato ime āsavā aparikkhīṇā”ti tatra vata maṃ samaṇo "
"vā brāhmaṇo vā devo vā māro vā brahmā vā koci vā lokasmiṃ sahadhammena "
"paṭicodessatī’ti nimittametaṃ, bhikkhave, na samanupassāmi."
msgstr ""
"I see no reason for anyone—whether ascetic, brahmin, god, Māra, or Brahmā, "
"or anyone else in the world—to legitimately scold me, saying: ‘You claim to "
"have ended all defilements, but these defilements have not ended.’"

msgctxt "an4.8:2.2"
msgid ""
"Etamahaṃ, bhikkhave, nimittaṃ asamanupassanto khemappatto abhayappatto "
"vesārajjappatto viharāmi."
msgstr "Since I see no such reason, I live secure, fearless, and assured."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
msgctxt "an4.8:3.1"
msgid ""
"‘“Ye kho pana te antarāyikā dhammā vuttā te paṭisevato nālaṃ antarāyāyā”ti "
"tatra vata maṃ samaṇo vā brāhmaṇo vā devo vā māro vā brahmā vā koci vā "
"lokasmiṃ sahadhammena paṭicodessatī’ti nimittametaṃ, bhikkhave, na "
"samanupassāmi."
msgstr ""
"I see no reason for anyone—whether ascetic, brahmin, god, Māra, or Brahmā, "
"or anyone else in the world—to legitimately scold me, saying: ‘The acts that "
"you say are obstructions are not really obstructions for the one who "
"performs them.’"

msgctxt "an4.8:3.2"
msgid ""
"Etamahaṃ, bhikkhave, nimittaṃ asamanupassanto khemappatto abhayappatto "
"vesārajjappatto viharāmi."
msgstr "Since I see no such reason, I live secure, fearless, and assured."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc4"></a>
msgctxt "an4.8:4.1"
msgid ""
"‘“Yassa kho pana te atthāya dhammo desito so na niyyāti takkarassa sammā "
"dukkhakkhayāyā”ti tatra vata maṃ samaṇo vā brāhmaṇo vā devo vā māro vā "
"brahmā vā koci vā lokasmiṃ sahadhammena paṭicodessatī’ti nimittametaṃ, "
"bhikkhave, na samanupassāmi."
msgstr ""
"I see no reason for anyone—whether ascetic, brahmin, god, Māra, or Brahmā, "
"or anyone else in the world—to legitimately scold me, saying: ‘Though you "
"teach that this teaching leads to the goal of the complete ending of "
"suffering, it doesn’t lead there for one who practices it.’"

msgctxt "an4.8:4.2"
msgid ""
"Etamahaṃ, bhikkhave, nimittaṃ asamanupassanto khemappatto abhayappatto "
"vesārajjappatto viharāmi."
msgstr "Since I see no such reason, I live secure, fearless, and assured."

msgctxt "an4.8:4.3"
msgid ""
"Imāni kho, bhikkhave, cattāri tathāgatassa vesārajjāni, yehi vesārajjehi "
"samannāgato tathāgato āsabhaṃ ṭhānaṃ paṭijānāti, parisāsu sīhanādaṃ nadati, "
"brahmacakkaṃ pavattetīti."
msgstr ""
"A Realized One has these four kinds of self-assurance. With these he claims "
"the bull’s place, roars his lion’s roar in the assemblies, and turns the "
"holy wheel."

#. </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc5"></a>
msgctxt "an4.8:5.1"
msgid "Ye kecime vādapathā puthussitā,"
msgstr "The various grounds for criticism"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an4.8:5.2"
msgid "Yaṃnissitā samaṇabrāhmaṇā ca;"
msgstr "that ascetics and brahmins rely on"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an4.8:5.3"
msgid "Tathāgataṃ patvā na te bhavanti,"
msgstr "don’t touch a Realized One,"

#. <br>
#. VAR: vādapathātivattaṃ → vādapathātivattinaṃ (bj) | vādapathāti vuttaṃ (pts1, mr)
msgctxt "an4.8:5.4"
msgid "Visāradaṃ vādapathātivattaṃ."
msgstr "assured, gone beyond grounds for criticism."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc6"></a>
#. VAR: kevalī → kevalaṃ (s1-3) | kevaliṃ (pts1) | kevalo (mr)
msgctxt "an4.8:6.1"
msgid "Yo dhammacakkaṃ abhibhuyya kevalī,"
msgstr "He rolls forth the Wheel of Dhamma as a consummate one,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an4.8:6.2"
msgid "Pavattayī sabbabhūtānukampī;"
msgstr "complete, compassionate for all living creatures."

#. <br>
msgctxt "an4.8:6.3"
msgid "Taṃ tādisaṃ devamanussaseṭṭhaṃ,"
msgstr "Sentient beings revere him, best of gods and humans,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an4.8:6.4"
msgid "Sattā namassanti bhavassa pāragun”ti."
msgstr "who has gone beyond rebirth.”"

#. </p></blockquote><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "an4.8:6.5"
msgid "Aṭṭhamaṃ."
msgstr ""
